The 40-year-old suspect is believed to have attacked the victim at the Yako informal settlement on Monday. CAPE TOWN - A man has been arrested for allegedly beating his girlfriend to death with a stick near Butterworth in the Eastern Cape.The 40-year-old suspect is believed to have attacked the victim at the Yako informal settlement on Monday.The woman sustained multiple wounds to her upper body.The police s Jackson Manatha said, We are informed they had a misunderstanding about money that he gave to his girlfriend at Yako informal settlement; because of that misunderstanding, he took a stick and severely assaulted the woman on her upper body and as a result she died instantly. 